      <hedline>
        <hl1>State Money for Crossroads</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PETER BELLER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Beller, Peter</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Gov Christine Whitman aproves $500,000 for Crossroads Theater Company in New Brunswick but rejects similar request from Paper Mill Playhouse in Millburn (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Governor Whitman late last month approved $500,000 for the Crossroads Theater Company in New Brunswick but turned down a similar request from the Paper Mill Playhouse in Millburn.</p>
        <p>Dale Caldwell, chief executive of Crossroads, said the money would go toward making late payments on the theater's debt, now about $1.7 million. The theater, which originally requested $1 million, had a budget of $2.7 million in the past but Mr. Caldwell estimates that that will drop.</p>
        <p>PETER BELLER</p>
      </block>
